oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of US Army Camp
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph shows rows of US or French tents with very muddy company streets running between them. A drainage ditch runs through the middle of the street. The soldiers appear in puttees and overseas caps which suggests that this camp was somewhere in France. The photograph was part of a larger collection belonging to Sgt. Ernest L. West, Batry. B, 114th F.A. Regt., 30th Div. The 30th Div. served under British command in France and fought at St. Mihiel and the Argonne Forest.
